          "__typename": "NodePage",
          "id": "page-about",
          "title": "About Oakridge School District",
          "path": "/about",
          "body": {
            "processed": "<p>Founded in 1952, Oakridge School District has been the cornerstone of education in our community for over seven decades. We serve more than 12,500 students across 18 schools, from pre-kindergarten through grade 12.</p><h2>Our Mission</h2><p>To inspire and prepare every student for success in college, career, and life through rigorous academics, enriching experiences, and a caring community.</p><h2>Our Values</h2><ul><li><strong>Excellence</strong> - We hold ourselves and our students to the highest standards.</li><li><strong>Equity</strong> - Every student deserves access to quality education regardless of background.</li><li><strong>Community</strong> - We build strong partnerships between schools, families, and the community.</li><li><strong>Innovation</strong> - We embrace new approaches to teaching and learning.</li></ul><h2>Accreditation</h2><p>All Oakridge schools are fully accredited by the Northwest Accreditation Commission.</p>",
            "summary": "Founded in 1952, Oakridge School District has been the cornerstone of education in our community for over seven decades. We serve more than 12,500 students across 18 schools, from pre-kindergarten thr"
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
